article.headline: Ohio 73, Duquesne 60
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Leon Williams scored all 13 of his points in the second half and added 18 rebounds, and Ohio defeated Duquesne 73-60 on Saturday. Williams' layup with 13:37 left broke a 43-43 tie, the 11th of the game, and sparked a 20-5 run over the next eight minutes that put Ohio up for good. Twelve points in the stretch came off offensive rebounds, as the Bobcats outrebounded the Dukes 48-23 for the game. Williams got in foul trouble early and played only seven minutes in the first half, when the Bobcats shot 32 percent to the Dukes' 44 percent for a 30-30 halftime tie. Mychal Green had 17 points and Sonny Troutman and Terren Harbut each added 12 for the Bobcats (4-2). Ohio shot 64 percent in a second-half turnaround as the Dukes fell to 29 percent. Duquesne (2-8) got 18 points each from Bryant McAllister and Jack Higgins, who was 4-of-8 on 3-pointers.
